values:
I haven't really updated on things I've done lately.

Well let's see. As of late I've left <b>Painkiller</b> forums for <b>SUGIZOLOVE.com</b> forums. Love it, love the Sugi, love the LS. <3 Nothing <i>too</i> exciting in my life really. Looking foward to D'espairsRay's first full album, Col:set ( wtf does that mean anyway? ). I'm hitting up AX this summer and I think that will be my last convention ever. Getting to old for this kiddy crap. :P

Only real fun thing I've done lately that I can think of is hang out with <b>Kuri of SUGIZOLOVE.com</b>. I hadn't seen her in two years, so it was a nice little "reunion" of sorts. Basically, we sat and oogled Sugizo for a good.. wow, well, long time. AndmadefunofRyuichiandInoran :X Then, we went food shopping ( I was the man and carried the bags XD ), followed by more.. SUGIZO AND LUNA SEA! ^O^ And some chinese food. :DDD She burnt me a ridiculous amount of LS and Sugizo videos. Everything from live stuff to PV's and TV appearances. It's been proven to me that Sugizo is quite the better guitarist than hide ( like I doubted that anyway. PSHHH )playing the solo from <b>X</b> ( the song ) BY HIMSELF and with ease. But yeah! Then I gave Kuri a big hug, called it a night and headed home. I was pretty beat. o_o;

All this LUNA SEA and early BUCK-TICK lately has made me realize just how little newer j-rock fans appreciate the roots of VK and j-rock. Some of them haven't even heard of BUCK-TICK and LUNA SEA. Sad, sad, soooo sad. -___-;
